OL,3,CMan guilty of murder after callously
OL,4,Cdisposing woman's body in his shed
OL,6,FHe later changed his story at trial,
OL,7,Fwhen the prosecution presented
OL,8,Fevidence which showed Barlow's DNA on
OL,9,Fthe woman's clothes and chest, saying
OL,10,Fhe found her dead and unclothed in his
OL,11,Fkitchen and panicked, putting her in
OL,12,Fhis shed and her clothes in the bin at
OL,13,Fhis home in Bolton.
OL,15,FMs Borocz was reported missing by her
OL,16,Ffamily on 15 December, 2024, and
OL,17,Fpolice enquiries found that she was
OL,18,Fseen leaving a shop with Barlow on
OL,19,FChorley Old Road, the day before.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
