OL,3,CMan guilty of murder after callously
OL,4,Cdisposing woman's body in his shed
OL,6,F"When police spoke to him as part of
OL,7,Ftheir missing person enquiries, he
OL,8,Flied to them also denying he had ever
OL,9,Fmet her.
OL,11,F"When Ms Borocz's body was found in
OL,12,Fhis shed, he claimed to have no
OL,13,Fknowledge of her being there, nor any
OL,14,Finvolvement in her death. He has shown
OL,15,Fno remorse for his actions and
OL,16,Fcontinually changed his account.
OL,18,F"Having heard the compelling evidence
OL,19,Fpresented by the Crown Prosecution
OL,20,FService, the jury found Barlow guilty
OL,21,Fof murder.
OL,26,@sD@AOUzD@AOU
