OL,3,CMan guilty of murder after callously
OL,4,Cdisposing woman's body in his shed
OL,6,F"Our thoughts remain with Ms Borocz's
OL,7,Ffamily for the loss they have endured,
OL,8,Fand we hope today's conviction will
OL,9,Fprovide some sense of justice for this
OL,10,Funspeakable crime."
OL,12,FMs Borocz's postmortem confirmed that
OL,13,Fthere was no evidence of recent head
OL,14,Finjury, heart attack or stroke, and
OL,15,Fthe prosecution made the case Barlow
OL,16,Fhad caused her death soon after she
OL,17,Farrived in his home, with the
OL,18,Fintention of causing her at least
OL,19,Fserious harm.
